    "content": "2.1.2  \u0007The 1990s—The birth of modern cybercrime\n\nAs the information revolution of the twenty-first century\nmatured, the nature of hacking underwent a significant trans-\nformation [34, 35]. While initially dominated by hobbyists\nand enthusiasts, there was a discernible shift towards more\norganised and often malevolent activities, particularly with\nthe emergence of criminal enterprises as central players in\nthe cyber threat arena [36]. Concurrently, the spectrum of\nmalicious software broadened [37, 37], with the introduc-\ntion of Trojans and the early variants of [38, 39], highlight-\ning the evolving sophistication and malicious intent behind\ncyberattacks [40].",
