    "content": "3.3  \u0007Data analysis\n\nWe used ChatGPT to categorise and classify the thematically\nextracted raw data (see Tables 4–8) according to the MITRE\nATT&CK Framework. The MITRE ATT&CK Framework is\na comprehensive and detailed knowledge base of adversary\ntactics and techniques used in real-world attacks [100]. It\ndescribes the actions that an attacker may take while oper-\nating within a network [101]. It is thus a valuable tool for\norganisations to understand and defend against cyberattacks\n[100, 101]. The MITRE ATT&CK Framework consists of\nthe following stages and are contrasted against the cyber kill\nchain [102, 103], in Table 4:",
