    "content": "In this section we aimed to present a nuanced understanding\nof the current landscape of AI-driven cyberattacks, including\nthe motivations behind such attacks, the mitigation strategies\nTable 4   MITRE ATT&CK Framework alongside the cyber kill chain\nCyber kill chain\nMITRE ATT&CK stage\nMITRE ATT&CK stage description\nReconnaissance\nReconnaissance\nGathering information about the target organisation and its environment\nResource development\nEstablishing the infrastructure and resources that will be needed to support the attack\nWeaponisation\nInitial access\nGaining access to the victim’s system\nExecution\nExecuting malicious code on the victim’s system\nPersistence\nMaintaining access to the victim’s system over time\nDelivery\nPrivilege escalation\nEscalating privileges to the highest possible level on the victim’s system\nDefence evasion\nEvading the victim's security defences\nExploitation\nCredential access\nGaining access to the victim’s credentials\nDiscovery\nDiscovering and enumerating the victim’s assets\nInstallation\nLateral movement\nMoving laterally across the victim’s network\nCollection\nCollecting data from the victim’s systems\nCommand and control\nCommand and control\nCommunicating with the victim’s systems to issue commands and receive data\nExfiltration\nExfiltration\nStealing data from the victim’s systems\nImpact\nCausing damage to the victim’s systems or data",
