    "content": "4.1  \u0007Types of AI‑driven cyberattacks\n\nThe paper's first research objective was to identify the dif-\nferent ways in which AI can be used to launch cyberattacks.\nThe offensive AI (deploys AI techniques to attack computer\nsystems and networks) and adversarial AI (maliciously\nexploits and/or attacks AI/ML systems and data) findings\nare presented in Table 5 and 6, respectively.\nHaving outlined the landscape of both offensive AI and its\nspecialised subset, adversarial AI, we now discuss the coun-\ntermeasures and mitigation strategies that can be deployed\nto defend against these advanced threats. The subsequent\nsection provides an in-depth analysis of various approaches\nto fortifying cyber defences against the onslaught of AI-\ndriven cyberattacks.",
