    "content": "In this paper, we introduce AutoBot, a framework to automatically\ndetect deceptive patterns on websites. AutoBot employs a modu-\nlar approach: first, it captures a screenshot of the website and pro-\ncesses it using the Vision Module to provide a textual representa-\ntion of the website (ElementMap). It then analyzes the ElementMap\nusing a Language Module to identify deceptive patterns and their\ntype. We evaluate AutoBot on a dataset of real-world websites to\ndemonstrate its accuracy in identifying and localizing deceptive\npatterns. We t hen i nstantiate A utoBot i n t hree s ettings: a user-\nfacing browser extension, a developer-facing Lighthouse report,\nand a researcher/regulator-facing website analysis tool.\nAcknowledgments\nThis work was supported by the NSF through awards CNS-1942014 and\nCNS-2247381, and by a research grant from the Google PSS Privacy Faculty\nAward program. Finally, we thank the reviewers for their thoughtful\nrecommendations.",
