    "content": "Ransomware\ndetection\nDeep Learning in\nCyber Security\nMalware\ndetection\nCyber threat\nsituational\nawareness\nNetwork traffic\nanalysis\nCryptography\nSteganography\nSteganalysis\nProtocol\nclassification\nApplication\nclassification\nBotnet\ndetection\nWindows\nmalware\ndetection\nAndroid\nmalware\ndetection\nFunction\nrecognition\nSpam\ndetection\nPhishing\ndetection\nSecurity log\ndata anaysis\nInsider threat\ndetection\nDGA domain\nname detection\nURL\nEmail\nImage spam\ndetection\nFig. 3. A hierarchical classification of DL Methods in Cyber Security.\nTABLE V\nSUMMARY OF STUDIES ON DL ARCHITECTURES AND DATASETS ADOPTED FOR INTRUSION DETECTION.\nReference\nArchitecture\nDataset\nCompared CML\n[201]\nRS\nKDDCup-99\nYes\n[211]\nDNN\nNSL-KDD\nNo\n[202]\nCNN, CNN-RS\nKDDCup-99\nNo\n[210]\nCNN\nNSL-KDD\nYes\n[208]\nAutoencoder\nNSL-KDD\nYes\n[203]\nRS\nNSL-KDD\nYes\n[222]\nDNN\nKDDCup-99\nYes\n[227]\nAutoEncoder\nKDDCup-99\nNo\n[204]\nCNN & RS\nDARPA1998 & ISCX-IDS-2012\nYes\n[205]\nRS & SVM\nKyoto\nNo\n[206]\nCNN\nBalabit, & TWOS\nNo\n[207]\nDNN\nCICIDS2017\nYes\n[227]\nAutoencoder\nNSL-KDD\nNo\n[212]\nCNN\nUNSW-NB15\nNo\n[213]\nCNN\nYes\n[214]\nRS\nISCX-IDS-2012 & AWID\nYes\n[215]\nCNN\nPrivate\nNo\n[216]\nDBN\nKDDCup-99, NSL-KDD, UNSW-NB15, CICIDS 2017\nYes\n[217]\nAutoencoder\nNSL-KDD & UNSW-NB15\nYes\n[218]\nCNN\nISCX-IDS-2012\nYes\n[219]\nDNN\nReal-time traffic, KDDCup-99, UNSW-NB15\nYes\n[220]\nRS & DNN\nCIDDS-001\nYes\n[221]\nSparse Autoencoder\nNSL-KDD\nYes\n[223]\nDBN, SAE, RS\nCTU-13\nNo\n[225]\nAutoencoder & DNN\nKDDCup-99, & UNSW-NB15\nYes\n[226]\nCNN & RS\nCICIDS2017\nNo\n[264]\nDNN, RS, CNN\nKDDCup 99 & Kyoto\nYes\n12) Mixed Dataset: DL studies compared with ML: A\nnovel CNN-LSTM based ID system was proposed with the\nCNN model to learn the low level spatial features and the\nLSTM model to learn the high level temporal features from\nthe network traffic data [204]. LSTM architectures for cyber\nattack detection in fog-of-things environment were proposed\nto be distributed and scalable to detect cyber-attacks [214].\nAnother distributed DBN with an ensemble SVM-based de-\ntection framework in a large scale network was proposed.\nThe distributed DBN was used for non-linear dimensionality\nreduction and an apache spark based ensemble SVM model\nwas used as a detection classifier. The model is trained on\n4 different datasets and compared with other related models\n[216]. In another study, anomaly based IDS using DAE\nand DNN was specifically designed for industrial Internet\nof things. The DAE model produced optimal parameters by\nlearning the normal behaviour of network which were used\nto effectively tune the parameters of DNN based classifier\n[217]. A scalable DNN based framework for routing attack\ndetection was proposed where the attack dataset was extracted\nfrom the Cooja IoT simulator [219]. A stack AE based NIDS\nwas proposed with learning of important features from a large\nquantity of unlabeled data using UNSW-NB15 and KDDCup-\n99 datasets achieved an accuracy of 89.134% and 99.996%\n勒索软件\n检测\n深度学习在\n网络安全\n恶意软件\n检测\n网络威胁\n态势\n感知\n网络流量\n分析\n密码学\n隐写术\n隐写分析\n协议\n分类\n应用\n分类\n僵尸网络\n检测\nWindows\n恶意软件\n检测\nAndroid\n恶意软件\n检测\n功能\n识别\nSpam\n检测\n网络钓鱼\n检测\n安全日志\n数据分析\n内部威胁\n检测\nDGA域名\n名称检测\nURL\n电子邮\n图像垃圾邮件\n检测",
