    "content": "行训练，第二层使用字节码语义，实现了97.74%的准确率\n[173]。\nF. 深度学习在侧信道攻击检测中\nction\n科赫在1996年引入了侧信道攻击，黑客曾利用这种攻击手\n段入侵密码设备[121]。侧信道信息硬件，如时序信息、电磁辐\n射、功耗以及加密设备的统计信息，都可能被黑客用来发起侧\n信道攻击。这类攻击速度极快且易于实施，对安全构成重大威\n胁。从小的嵌入式设备如RFID到笔记本电脑等任何设备，都可\n能受到侧信道攻击的威胁。我们回顾了关于深度学习框架用于\n有效检测侧信道攻击的研究，并在表X中进行了总结。\nBLE IX\nTIONS IN ANDROID MALWARE DETECTION.\nArchitecture\nDataset\nCompared\nCML\nDBN\nPublically available sources\nYes\nAutoencoder\nPublically available sources\nNo\nDBN\nPublically available sources\nYes\nSAE\nPublically available sources\nYes\nDNN\nDrebin, collected from PASs\nYes\npcode\nCNN\nPublically available sources\nNo\nCNN\nPublically available sources\nYes\nd images\nCNN\nCollected by the researchers\nNo\nCNN\nPublically available sources\nYes\nmissions\nDBN\nDrebin, apps collected from PASs\nNo\nions\nalls,\nPI calls,\nCNN\nPublically available sources\nYes\nCNN\nDrebin, apps collected from PASs\nNo\nbytecode\nCNN-RS\nPublically available sources\nNo\nRS\nPublically available sources\nYes\nmali\nDNN\nPrivate\nYes\nCNN\nDrebin, collected from PASs\nYes\nCNN\nPublically available sources\nNo\nCNN\nAMD, AndroZoo,\nDrebin Malware Collection,\nISCX Android Botnet\nYes\nmalware detection framework used opcode sequences from\ndecompiled APK files for training and achieved a detection\naccuracy of 99% with very low false positives [176].\nDL models without comparing with ML: A CNN based\nandroid malware detection framework trained using features\nfrom static analysis of raw opcode sequences was computa-\ntionally more efficient when compared to n-gram based de-\ntection models [170]. In another study, a DBN-based android\nmalware detection system extracted features from API calls\nand permissions to build the detection model. While DREBIN\nattained accuracy of 90% with 545000 features, the DBN\nmodel achieved the same accuracy with just 237 features\n[166].\nA DL based automatic malware detection frame-work for\nandroid systems was proposed for deployment on servers,\nmobile and 